It turns out you need to explicitly catch `NoSuchMethodError` as follows

```java
...
try {
   verifyDeployment(pipelineParams)
} catch (NoSuchMethodError ex) {
   echo &quot;[INFO] No `verifyDeployment` defined, thus ignoring this step&quot;
}
...
```

You are using a wrong groovy syntax. 
See the correct groovy syntax for catching exceptions: [Syntax catching exceptions][1] 

    try { 
       //Protected code 
    } catch(ExceptionName e1) {
       //Catch block 
    }

  [1]: http://tutorialspoint.com/groovy/groovy_exception_handling.htm

