According to documentation for [BottomNavigationBar][1], if there more then three BottomNavigationBarItems then BottomNavigationBarType.shifting type is used.

This shifting type renders all items in white if selectedItemColor is null. 

You will need to add selectedColor property for BottomNavigationBar widget to change this behavior as below:

    bottomNavigationBar: BottomNavigationBar(
          //Selected items color gives color to the BottomNavigationBarItem&#39;s title widget, which is currently selected
          selectedItemColor: Colors.blue,
          //Selected icons theme gives icon theme the BottomNavigationBarItem&#39;s icon widget, which is currently selected
          selectedIconTheme: IconThemeData(
            color: Colors.blue,
            opacity: 1.0,
            size: 30.0
          ),
          //unselected items color gives color to the BottomNavigationBarItem&#39;s title widget, which is currently unselected
          unselectedItemColor: Colors.black,
          //unselected icons theme gives icon theme the BottomNavigationBarItem&#39;s icon widget, which is currently unselected
          unselectedIconTheme: IconThemeData(
                color: Colors.black,
                opacity: 1.0,
                size: 30.0
          ),
          items: [
            BottomNavigationBarItem(
              icon: Icon(Icons.category),
              title: Text(&#39;categoris&#39;),
